WEBVTT

00:00.517 --> 00:01.916
<i>Previously on</i>
Two and a Half Men...

00:02.111 --> 00:03.878
Excuse me, do you know
the difference

00:03.903 --> 00:06.353
between "organic beef"
and "grass-fed beef"?

00:07.040 --> 00:08.239
She was totally hitting on you.

00:08.325 --> 00:09.909
You should ask her out.

00:10.058 --> 00:12.809
Hey, Zoey, you want
to on a date with me?!

00:12.811 --> 00:14.261
Sure!

00:14.263 --> 00:16.880
When I was in high school,
I met this girl named Bridget.

00:16.882 --> 00:18.915
You're still in love
with her, aren't you?

00:18.917 --> 00:20.383
See, look. No wedding ring.

00:20.385 --> 00:22.586
Hmm, I noticed
the bright white tan line.

00:22.588 --> 00:24.387
No worries. I gave it to Alan.

00:24.389 --> 00:27.224
Oh... very valuable.

00:27.226 --> 00:28.842
(chuckles)

00:28.844 --> 00:30.677
You seem like
a really sweet guy,

00:30.679 --> 00:34.514
but I think you're still kind
of married to your Bridget.

00:34.516 --> 00:37.651
Face it, you're not ready
to be dating yet.

00:38.769 --> 00:40.970
You want your ring back?

00:40.972 --> 00:42.072
Yeah.

00:42.074 --> 00:43.640
I don't need this anymore.

00:43.642 --> 00:44.908
You sure?

00:44.910 --> 00:47.244
I'm positive.

00:48.312 --> 00:50.614
My precious! My precious!

00:53.501 --> 00:56.152
My precious! My precious!

00:58.289 --> 01:00.624
My precious!

01:05.212 --> 01:07.180
Mind if I take this?

01:07.182 --> 01:09.132
Oh, uh, no--
somebody's sitting there.

01:09.134 --> 01:11.334
Well, where are they?

01:11.336 --> 01:12.636
They're not here yet.

01:12.638 --> 01:14.938
Well, I'm here
and I need a chair.

01:14.940 --> 01:16.640
No, uh...

01:16.642 --> 01:18.775
honestly, I have a girl coming.

01:18.777 --> 01:21.444
Well, when she gets here,
I'll give it back to her.

01:21.446 --> 01:24.698
See, I don't believe that.

01:27.017 --> 01:29.202
You calling me a liar?

01:29.204 --> 01:33.490
No, but I've been burnt before.

01:33.492 --> 01:36.025
I'm taking this chair.

01:36.027 --> 01:37.544
No, you're not.

01:37.546 --> 01:39.913
Yes, I am. Let go!

01:39.915 --> 01:41.247
You let go
of the chair.

01:41.249 --> 01:42.966
I had the chair before
you even came into the place.

01:42.968 --> 01:44.551
- It's mine now!
- It's my chair now!

01:44.553 --> 01:46.469
Walden, is everything all right?

01:46.471 --> 01:48.488
Ha! She's here.
Now back off!

01:50.257 --> 01:51.558
What was that all about?

01:51.560 --> 01:53.560
It was an attempt
at a chairjacking.

01:53.562 --> 01:56.146
Here, I get you a tea.

01:56.148 --> 01:58.431
Thank you.
I'm sorry I'm late.

01:58.433 --> 02:00.734
I'm trying to get my daughter
into Bellwood Academy.

02:00.736 --> 02:02.485
It's a nightmare.

02:02.487 --> 02:05.188
She tests well, but she did
not give a good interview.

02:05.190 --> 02:06.389
How old is
your daughter again?

02:06.391 --> 02:08.024
Five.

02:08.026 --> 02:11.194
And Bellwood Academy is a...?
Kindergarten.

02:11.196 --> 02:14.414
Wow, when I was five,
I got kicked out of preschool

02:14.416 --> 02:15.532
for biting my teacher.

02:15.534 --> 02:16.866
Why did you bite her?

02:16.868 --> 02:18.752
She tried to steal my chair.

02:20.404 --> 02:22.071
Yeah, you heard me! I bit her!

02:23.507 --> 02:24.907
She had to get a shot!

02:27.011 --> 02:28.678
Take it easy, okay?

02:29.930 --> 02:31.381
So I was rather surprised

02:31.383 --> 02:32.882
to hear from you.
What's up?

02:32.884 --> 02:35.969
I was thinking a lot about what
you said about not wanting

02:35.971 --> 02:39.422
to date me while I was
still, you know,

02:39.424 --> 02:41.090
emotionally attached
to my ex-wife.

02:41.092 --> 02:44.027
I said you were still
hopelessly in love with her.

02:44.029 --> 02:46.730
Potato, Po-tah-to.

02:46.732 --> 02:48.264
The point is you were right.

02:48.266 --> 02:50.483
I wasn't ready to start
dating, but I am now.

02:50.485 --> 02:53.236
A whole week later.

02:53.238 --> 02:55.038
I understand your skepticism.

02:55.040 --> 02:57.907
Which is why I want you to
witness what I'm about to do.

02:57.909 --> 02:59.876
These...

02:59.878 --> 03:02.295
are my final divorce papers.

03:03.414 --> 03:07.384
And once I sign them, my
marriage will be over forever.

03:08.586 --> 03:11.638
I was hoping that you
and I could start fresh.

03:11.640 --> 03:14.674
Nothing like starting off
a new relationship

03:14.676 --> 03:16.459
on the ashes of the old one.

03:16.461 --> 03:18.961
That's what I was thinking.

03:21.799 --> 03:23.316
Oh, uh, you got a pen?

03:23.318 --> 03:25.735
Uh, I don't think I do.

03:25.737 --> 03:26.803
Okay.

03:26.805 --> 03:29.138
Uh, does anybody got a pen
I can borrow?

03:30.157 --> 03:32.141
Anyone? Nobody?

03:32.143 --> 03:33.142
Excuse me.

03:33.144 --> 03:34.077
Do you got a pen?

03:34.079 --> 03:35.144
Sorry.

03:35.146 --> 03:38.114
It's unbelievable.

03:38.116 --> 03:39.783
(clears throat)

03:41.001 --> 03:43.986
Oh, man.

03:43.988 --> 03:46.089
Can I please borrow your pen?

03:46.091 --> 03:49.676
I'm sorry, someone's using it.

03:49.678 --> 03:50.960
Who?

03:50.962 --> 03:53.480
They're not here yet.

03:54.782 --> 03:57.667
I will give you a hundred
dollars to borrow that pen.

03:57.669 --> 03:59.769
(patrons clamoring)

